1. Access. 
In consideration for being granted access to the Site, you (and your firm, if you represent a firm) (“you”) agree and acknowledge, at the time of initial access and on an ongoing basis, that you have read and understand the Terms and Conditions, and agree to be bound hereby.  Your subsequent access to the Site shall be deemed to constitute full acceptance by you of the Terms and Conditions. You agree that Legion Partners will not be liable for any loss or damage arising from your use of the information contained on the Site.
2. Modifications. 
Legion Partners may revise or remove any part of the Terms and Conditions, in its sole discretion, at any time, and without prior notice to you, by updating this posted version of the Terms and Conditions. You are responsible for regularly reviewing the Site for changes to the Terms and Conditions. Any changes are effective upon posting to the Site. IF YOU ARE DISSATISFIED OR DISAGREE WITH ANY CHANGES, YOUR SOLE AND EXCLUSIVE REMEDY IS TO TERMINATE YOUR USE OF THE SITE. Your continued use after a change has been posted constitutes your acceptance of those changes. 
3. Internet.
Use of the Internet is solely at your own risk and is subject to all applicable Laws (as defined below). Legion Partners has attempted to create a secure and reliable website, however, it is important to be aware that the confidentiality or privacy of any communication transmitted to or from the Site and over the Internet cannot be guaranteed. In this regard, you acknowledge and agree that, to the extent that the transfer of information to and from the Site is dependent on the use of the Internet, such information may be adversely affected by, among other risks, breaches in security, temporary loss, delay or inconsistency of service, loss of data and/or business interruption, and uncertain legal, regulatory and tax issues concerning the use of the Internet, all of which are beyond Legion Partners’ control. Legion Partners shall not be liable for any losses, damages, costs or expenses of any nature incurred by you or any other person as a result of your use of the Internet to access the Site.
4. Grant of License. 
You are provided with a limited, revocable, nonexclusive and nontransferable license to the Site conditioned upon your continued compliance with the Terms and Conditions. You may not sell, lease or rent access to or use of the Site. You shall not use the Site at any time for any purpose that is unlawful or prohibited and you shall comply with any applicable local, state, national or international statutes, rules, regulations, ordinances, decrees, laws, codes, orders, regulations, or treaties (“Laws”) when using the Site.
